<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="271" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="3.[136,1452,158,1301]" pageId="3" pageNumber="271">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,261,158,184]" pageId="3" pageNumber="271">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
— 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="271">
Recedit ab Limonio todaroano habito dense pulvinato, foliis viridibus, 1-nerviis, 
<quantity box="[1172,1280,158,184]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="271" unit="cm" value="30.0" valueMax="50.0" valueMin="10.0">10–50 cm</quantity>
longis, 
<quantity box="[1364,1451,158,184]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" metricValueMax="8.0" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="271" unit="mm" value="5.5" valueMax="8.0" valueMin="3.0">3–8 mm</quantity>
latis, rotundatis vel subobtusis, leviter revolutis margine, scapis rugoso-striatis, ramis sterilibus simplicibus aliquot, spicis 
<quantity box="[208,312,230,256]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.25" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="0.5" pageId="3" pageNumber="271" unit="mm" value="12.5" valueMax="20.0" valueMin="5.0">5–20 mm</quantity>
longis, spiculis 
<quantity box="[498,588,230,256]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" metricValueMax="6.0" metricValueMin="5.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="271" unit="mm" value="5.5" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="5.0">5–6 mm</quantity>
longis, 2-floris, ad 
<quantity box="[813,885,230,256]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.651" metricValueMax="1.778" metricValueMin="1.524" pageId="3" pageNumber="271" unit="in" value="6.5" valueMax="7.0" valueMin="6.0">6–7 in</quantity>
1 centimetro dispositis, bractea inferiore 2–2.5 × 
<quantity box="[136,248,266,292]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.75" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="1.5" pageId="3" pageNumber="271" unit="mm" value="1.75" valueMax="2.0" valueMin="1.5">1.5–2 mm</quantity>
, bractea media denticulata apice, bractea superiore apiculo centrali attingens marginem superiorem, calyce 
<quantity box="[136,246,302,328]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.25" metricValueMax="4.5" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="271" unit="mm" value="4.25" valueMax="4.5" valueMin="4.0">4–4.5 mm</quantity>
longo, ex bractea superiore 
<quantity box="[569,700,302,328]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.65" metricValueMax="1.8" metricValueMin="1.5" pageId="3" pageNumber="271" unit="mm" value="1.65" valueMax="1.8" valueMin="1.5">1.5–1.8 mm</quantity>
exserto, tubo unilateraliter dense piloso et lobis triangularibus
</emphasis>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="271" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="3.[136,1452,158,1301]" pageId="3" pageNumber="271">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,337,338,364]" pageId="3" pageNumber="271">Description:</emphasis>
—Plant perennial, glabrous, forming a sub-shrub densely pulvinate, 
<quantity box="[1093,1202,338,365]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="271" unit="cm" value="40.0" valueMax="50.0" valueMin="30.0">30–50 cm</quantity>
tall, with several erect stems and a very robust tap-root. Caudices 
<quantity box="[624,735,374,401]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="271" unit="cm" value="15.0" valueMax="20.0" valueMin="10.0">10–20 cm</quantity>
long, branched, densely spirally leafy mainly in the upper half, living leaves in apical rosettes. Leaves fleshy, green, slightly rugose, 
<quantity box="[905,1025,410,437]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="271" unit="mm" value="30.0" valueMax="50.0" valueMin="10.0">10–50 mm</quantity>
long and 
<quantity box="[1134,1227,410,437]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" metricValueMax="8.0" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="271" unit="mm" value="5.5" valueMax="8.0" valueMin="3.0">3–8 mm</quantity>
wide, oblanceolatespathulate, rounded to subobtuse at apex, slightly revolute at margin, uninerved, gradually tapering into the petiole. Stems green, rugose-striate, 
<quantity box="[462,576,482,509]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.35" metricValueMax="3.5" metricValueMin="1.2" pageId="3" pageNumber="271" unit="cm" value="23.5" valueMax="35.0" valueMin="12.0">12–35 cm</quantity>
long, slightly flexuous, often branched from the base, with several simplex sterile branches, 0.5–5.0 cm long. Inflorescence terminal, few branched, with branches sub-erect, the lower long pedicelled, the upper with pedicel progressively reduced. Spikes 
<quantity box="[893,1004,554,581]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.25" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="0.5" pageId="3" pageNumber="271" unit="mm" value="12.5" valueMax="20.0" valueMin="5.0">5–20 mm</quantity>
long, straight to slightly curved, erect to directed obliquely upwards; axis of spike rugose. Spikelets 
<quantity box="[849,943,590,617]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" metricValueMax="6.0" metricValueMin="5.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="271" unit="mm" value="5.5" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="5.0">5–6 mm</quantity>
long, 2-flowered, densely arranged, 6–7 per 
<quantity box="[136,197,626,653]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="271" unit="cm" value="1.0">1 cm</quantity>
. Outer bract 2.0– 
<quantity box="[397,485,626,653]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" pageId="3" pageNumber="271" unit="mm" value="2.5">2.5 mm</quantity>
long and 1.5–2.0 mm wide at the base, triangular-ovate, acute, with margin broadly membranous and central part fleshy, acuminate up to the apex. Middle bract membranous, 2.0–2.2 × 
<quantity box="[1307,1447,662,689]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" metricValueMax="1.3" metricValueMin="1.1" pageId="3" pageNumber="271" unit="mm" value="1.2" valueMax="1.3" valueMin="1.1">1.1–1.3 mm</quantity>
, oblong-elliptic, rounded-denticulate at the apex. Inner bract 4.2–5.0 × 
<quantity box="[913,1048,698,725]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.6" metricValueMax="2.7" metricValueMin="2.5" pageId="3" pageNumber="271" unit="mm" value="2.6" valueMax="2.7" valueMin="2.5">2.5–2.7 mm</quantity>
, oblong, rounded, with margin more or less broadly membranous, central part fleshy, lanceolate, acuminate, forming a narrowly triangular tip, 1.0– 
<quantity box="[1367,1452,734,761]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" pageId="3" pageNumber="271" unit="mm" value="1.2">1.2 mm</quantity>
long, reaching the upper margin. Calyx 4.0– 
<quantity box="[630,714,770,797]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" pageId="3" pageNumber="271" unit="mm" value="4.5">4.5 mm</quantity>
long, exceeding the inner bract by 
<quantity box="[1107,1243,770,797]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.65" metricValueMax="1.8" metricValueMin="1.5" pageId="3" pageNumber="271" unit="mm" value="1.65" valueMax="1.8" valueMin="1.5">1.5–1.8 mm</quantity>
, with tube densely hairy only from one side and 5 ribs ending at the base of lobes; calyx lobes triangular, 0.6–0.8 × 
<quantity box="[1219,1357,806,833]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.0" metricValueMax="8.0" metricValueMin="6.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="271" unit="mm" value="0.7" valueMax="0.8" valueMin="0.6">0.6–0.8 mm</quantity>
. Corolla pale violet.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[136,1452,158,1301]" box="[189,606,878,904]" pageId="3" pageNumber="271">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,460,878,904]" pageId="3" pageNumber="271">Chromosome number:</emphasis>
—Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="273" pageId="3" pageNumber="271" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="3.[136,1452,158,1301]" pageId="3" pageNumber="271">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,328,914,940]" pageId="3" pageNumber="271">Etymology:</emphasis>
—The specific epithet is derived from the ancient Greek “poimen”, which means shepherd. It refers to “Monte Pecoraro” (in English Mt. Shepherd), the locus classicus of 
<taxonomicName box="[927,1073,951,976]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plumbaginaceae" genus="Limonium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="3" pageNumber="271" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="poimenum">
<emphasis box="[927,1073,951,976]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="271">L. poimenum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[136,1452,158,1301]" box="[189,882,986,1013]" pageId="3" pageNumber="271">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,323,986,1012]" pageId="3" pageNumber="271">Phenology:</emphasis>
—Flowering July−August, fruiting up to October.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[136,1452,158,1301]" pageId="3" pageNumber="271">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,480,1022,1048]" pageId="3" pageNumber="271">Habitat and distribution</emphasis>
—It is a rare endemic chasmophyte restricted to the calcareous cliff facing the airport of Palermo near Punta Raisi (NW 
<collectingRegion box="[489,555,1058,1084]" country="Italy" name="Sicilia" pageId="3" pageNumber="271">Sicily</collectingRegion>
, 
<figureCitation box="[566,633,1058,1084]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="3.[136,229,2064,2086]" captionTargetBox="[341,1248,1325,2039]" captionTargetId="figure-521@3.[339,1248,1325,2039]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 3. Geographical distribution of Limonium poimenum (circle) and L. todaroanum (square)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5147516" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5147516/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="271">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
). This new species grows in the crevices of more or less vertical surfaces at an elevation of 
<quantity box="[344,475,1094,1121]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.0" metricValueMax="7.5" metricValueMin="6.5" pageId="3" pageNumber="271" unit="m" value="700.0" valueMax="750.0" valueMin="650.0">650−750 m</quantity>
a.s.l. The cliff has a western aspect, and is usually affected by a regime of dense fog due to the humid winds coming from the Tyrrhenian Sea. 
<taxonomicName box="[789,937,1131,1156]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plumbaginaceae" genus="Limonium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="3" pageNumber="271" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="poimenum">
<emphasis box="[789,937,1131,1156]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="271">L. poimenum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a member of a rupestrian plant community characterized by numerous endemics linked to these habitats, such as 
<taxonomicName authority="Lojacono (1903: 137)" authorityName="Lojacono" authorityPageNumber="137" authorityYear="1903" box="[922,1447,1166,1193]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Centaurea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="3" pageNumber="271" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="panormitana">
<emphasis box="[922,1192,1167,1193]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="271">Centaurea panormitana</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Lojacono Pojero, M." box="[1199,1447,1166,1192]" pageId="3" pageNumber="271" refId="ref2727" refString="Lojacono Pojero, M. (1903) Flora Sicula 2 (1). Tipo-Litografia Salvatore Bizzarilli, Palermo, 240 pp." type="book" year="1903">Lojacono (1903: 137)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Tineo ex Gussone (1844: 467) subsp. panormitanum" authorityName="Tineo ex Gussone" authorityYear="1844" box="[136,1047,1202,1229]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Helichrysum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="3" pageNumber="271" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="panormitanum" subSpecies="panormitanum">
<emphasis box="[136,451,1202,1228]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="271">Helichrysum panormitanum</emphasis>
Tineo ex 
<bibRefCitation author="Gussone, G." box="[562,798,1202,1229]" pageId="3" pageNumber="271" refId="ref2470" refString="Gussone, G. (1844) Flora Sicula Synopsis 2 (1). Ex Typis Tramater, Neapoli, 530 pp." type="book" year="1844">Gussone (1844: 467)</bibRefCitation>
subsp. 
<emphasis box="[882,1047,1203,1228]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="271">panormitanum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Linnaeus 1753: 100) Greuter &amp; Burdet (1985: 74)" authorityName="Greuter &amp; Burdet" authorityPageNumber="74" authorityYear="1985" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityPageNumber="100" baseAuthorityYear="1753" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Caprifoliaceae" genus="Lomelosia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Dipsacales" pageId="3" pageNumber="271" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cretica">
<emphasis box="[1061,1262,1202,1228]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="271">Lomelosia cretica</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Linnaeus" pageId="3" pageNumber="271" refId="ref2549" refString="Linnaeus (1753) Species Plantarum 1. Imprensis Laurentii Salvii, Holmiae, 560 pp." type="book" year="1753">Linnaeus 1753: 100</bibRefCitation>
) 
<bibRefCitation author="Greuter, W. &amp; Burdet, H. M." box="[195,522,1238,1265]" pageId="3" pageNumber="271" pagination="73 - 76" refId="ref2355" refString="Greuter, W. &amp; Burdet, H. M. (1985) Lomelosia. In: Greuter, W. &amp; Raus, Th. (Eds.) Med-Checklist Notulae, 11. Willdenowia 15 (1): 73 - 76." type="journal article" year="1985">Greuter &amp; Burdet (1985: 74)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Gussone (1821: 80)" authorityName="Gussone" authorityPageNumber="80" authorityYear="1821" box="[534,941,1238,1264]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apiaceae" genus="Seseli" kingdom="Plantae" order="Apiales" pageId="3" pageNumber="271" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bocconei">
