<paragraph blockId="5.[136,1452,158,797]" pageId="5" pageNumber="273">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,435,158,184]" pageId="5" pageNumber="273">Conservation status:</emphasis>
—According to the IUCN Red list category and criteria (
<bibRefCitation author="IUCN" box="[1061,1197,158,184]" pageId="5" pageNumber="273" refId="ref2494" refString="IUCN (2014) Guidelines for Using the IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria. Version 11. Prepared by the Standards and Petitions Subcommittee, Cambridge U. K. Available from: http: // jr. iucnredlist. org / documents / RedListGuidelines. pdf (accessed 10 October 2014)." type="book" year="2014">IUCN 2014</bibRefCitation>
), 
<taxonomicName box="[1215,1452,159,184]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plumbaginaceae" genus="Limonium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="5" pageNumber="273" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="poimenum">
<emphasis box="[1215,1452,159,184]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="273">Limonium poimenum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
should be treated as Endangered: EN (criterion D), because of the low number of individuals (less than 100) and the very limited distribution (less than 
<quantity box="[529,586,230,256]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="273" unit="km" value="1.0">1 km</quantity>
<superScript attach="left" box="[586,594,230,244]" fontSize="6" pageId="5" pageNumber="273">2</superScript>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[136,1452,158,797]" pageId="5" pageNumber="273">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,423,266,292]" pageId="5" pageNumber="273">Taxonomical notes:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName box="[451,691,267,292]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plumbaginaceae" genus="Limonium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="5" pageNumber="273" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="poimenum">
<emphasis box="[451,691,267,292]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="273">Limonium poimenum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
belongs to the subgenus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Miller (1754:" authorityYear="1328" box="[984,1098,267,292]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plumbaginaceae" genus="Limonium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="5" pageNumber="273" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[984,1098,267,292]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="273">Limonium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and it is morphologically well different from other species by a pool of diacritical characters: the dense shrubby pulvinate habit, few branched and poor inflorescence, leaves densely arranged along the caudices, dense and very short spikes. Among the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Miller (1754:" authorityYear="1328" box="[1338,1452,339,364]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plumbaginaceae" genus="Limonium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="5" pageNumber="273" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1338,1452,339,364]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="273">Limonium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
occurring in 
<collectingRegion box="[280,346,374,400]" country="Italy" name="Sicilia" pageId="5" pageNumber="273">Sicily</collectingRegion>
, this new species shows some relationships mostly with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Raimondo &amp; Pignatti" authorityYear="1986" box="[982,1148,374,400]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plumbaginaceae" genus="Limonium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="5" pageNumber="273" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="todaroanum">
<emphasis box="[982,1148,374,400]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="273">L. todaroanum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which grows at Mt. Passo del Lupo (San Vito Lo Capo, NW 
<collectingRegion box="[513,580,410,437]" country="Italy" name="Sicilia" pageId="5" pageNumber="273">Sicily</collectingRegion>
) not far from Mt. Pecoraro (
<figureCitation box="[893,960,410,436]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="3.[136,229,2064,2086]" captionTargetBox="[341,1248,1325,2039]" captionTargetId="figure-521@3.[339,1248,1325,2039]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 3. Geographical distribution of Limonium poimenum (circle) and L. todaroanum (square)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5147516" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5147516/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="273">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName box="[980,1131,410,436]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plumbaginaceae" genus="Limonium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="5" pageNumber="273" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="todaroanm">
<emphasis box="[980,1131,410,436]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="273">L. todaroanm</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
also grows in the crevices of a calcareous cliff of a mountain near Trapani at a elevation of about 
<quantity box="[904,975,446,473]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="273" unit="m" value="700.0">700 m</quantity>
a.s.l., together with several other endemic chasmophytes. Despite this 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Raimondo &amp; Pignatti" authorityYear="1986" box="[446,611,482,508]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plumbaginaceae" genus="Limonium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="5" pageNumber="273" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="todaroanum">
<emphasis box="[446,611,482,508]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="273">L. todaroanum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
clearly differs from 
<taxonomicName box="[839,985,483,508]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plumbaginaceae" genus="Limonium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="5" pageNumber="273" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="poimenum">
<emphasis box="[839,985,483,508]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="273">L. poimenum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having a habit lax not pulvinate, leaves dark green, (1–)3-nerved, obtuse (rarely rounded or retuse), (20–)30–70 × 
<quantity box="[999,1110,518,545]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.5" metricValueMax="12.0" metricValueMin="7.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="273" unit="mm" value="9.5" valueMax="12.0" valueMin="7.0">7–12 mm</quantity>
, flat, stems slightly scabrous, sterile branches absent o rare, spikes longer and lax, 
<quantity box="[739,823,554,581]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" metricValueMax="6.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="273" unit="cm" value="4.0" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="2.0">2–6 cm</quantity>
long, with 2–4(–5) spikelets per 
<quantity box="[1203,1262,554,581]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="273" unit="cm" value="1.0">1 cm</quantity>
, spikelets (2–)3- lowered, 
<quantity box="[241,334,590,617]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.5" metricValueMax="8.0" metricValueMin="7.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="273" unit="mm" value="7.5" valueMax="8.0" valueMin="7.0">7–8 mm</quantity>
long, outer bract 1.5–2 × 
<quantity box="[628,765,590,617]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.4" metricValueMax="1.5" metricValueMin="1.3" pageId="5" pageNumber="273" unit="mm" value="1.4" valueMax="1.5" valueMin="1.3">1.3–1.5 mm</quantity>
, middle bract smooth at the apex, inner bract with central tip 0.9–1.0 mm long, not reaching the upper margin; calyx 
<quantity box="[757,850,626,653]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" metricValueMax="7.0" metricValueMin="5.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="273" unit="mm" value="6.0" valueMax="7.0" valueMin="5.0">5–7 mm</quantity>
long, exceeding the inner bract by 
<quantity box="[1241,1336,626,653]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" metricValueMax="3.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="273" unit="mm" value="2.5" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="2.0">2–3 mm</quantity>
, with tube sparsely hairy at the base and lobes subrounded (
<figureCitation box="[706,809,662,688]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="2.[136,226,2028,2050]" captionTargetBox="[435,1153,191,2004]" captionTargetId="figure-18@2.[435,1153,190,2004]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 2. Phenological features of Limonium poimenum and L. todaroanum. A. Rupestrian habitat of L. poimenum (Monte Pecoraro). B. Habit of L. poimenum. C. Inflorescence of L. poimenum. D. Inflorescence of L. todaroanum. (A–C: photos by V. Ilardi, D: photo by S. Brullo)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5147514" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5147514/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="273">Figs. 2D</figureCitation>
, 
